BBC.Rugby.Union.2014.11.08.Wales.v.Australia.720p.h264-NX

BBC 1 HD 8th Nov 2014
2pm to 4:30pm Live

John Inverdale presents live coverage as Wales begin their autumn international campaign by taking on Australia at the Millennium Stadium. Warren Gatland's side are on a nine-game losing streak against the Wallabies, a run which stretches back to 2008. But the visitors are by no means invincible, having lost a Rugby Championship game to Argentina for the first time in October. Match commentary and expert analysis comes from Eddie Butler, Jonathan Davies, Jeremy Guscott, Martyn Williams and Keith Wood.
